The pGL3 luciferase reporter vector (Promega, USA) was used as the cloning vector for the reporter gene assay to analyze the potential target region of miR-223. A 120-bp fragment containing the predicted miR-223 binding sites of the STMN1 3′UTR was amplified by PCR using cDNA and the primers STMN1 3′UTR-forward and STMN1 3′UTR-reverse (Table S1). The product was subcloned into the KpnI and XhoI sites of the pGL3-basic vector to generate the reporter plasmid pGLuc-STMN1 3′UTR. Another five primers, STMN1 3′UTR-forward2, STMN1 3′UTR-mutant1-forward, STMN1 3′UTR-mutant1-reverse, STMN1 3′UTR-mutant2-forward, and STMN1 3′UTR-mutant2-reverse (Table S1), were used to generate plasmids expressing mutant sequences. The corresponding mutant constructs, pGLuc-STMN1 3′UTR-mutant1 and pGLuc-STMN1 3′UTR-mutant2, were created by deleting or mutating the binding sites for the seed region of miR-223 (Fig. 3
A
). All constructs were confirmed by DNA sequencing.
